Vcs-Browser: https://codeberg.org/foopgp/bash-libs

Package: bashlibs-all
Architecture: all
Depends: bashlibs-common, bashlibs-convert, bashlibs-pgpid, bashlibs-dji,
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: bash-libs: set of bash executables which may also be sourced as libraries.
 This metapackage install all the bash libraries used by foopgp on the Debian blend
 « Djibian ».

Package: bashlibs-common
Architecture: all
Depends: bsdutils (>= 3.0-0), aspell, xxd,
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: bash-completion, whiptail
Description: bash-libs: set of bash executables which may also be sourced as libraries.
 This package contains:
 .
 bl-log: Wrapper for logger command, which also print pretty logs on stderr.
 .
 bl-interactive: Help managing interactive choices,
 while supporting multiple frontends: NONE, zenity, whiptail or dialog.
 .
 bl-security: Provide some security features, notably a passphrase generator.

Package: bashlibs-convert
Architecture: all
Depends: jq,
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: bash-completion
Description: bash-libs: set of bash executables which may also be sourced as libraries.
 This package contains:
 .
 bl-markdown: Manipulate [markdown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown).
 Today, only converts: markdown arrays <> bash arrays.
 .
 bl-json: Use jq (Command-line JSON processor) to convert json data
 to bash variables or arrays, and vice-versa.

Package: bashlibs-pgpid
Architecture: all
Depends: bashlibs-common, gpg, xxd, adduser, passwd, curl, qrencode, graphicsmagick,
         libgfshare-bin, pandoc, texlive-extra-utils, cups-client, cups-bsd, zbar-tools,
         texlive-latex-recommended, scdaemon,
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: bash-completion
Description: bash-libs: set of bash executables which may also be sourced as libraries.
 This package contains:
 .
 bl-pgpid: Generate and manage OpenPGP ID, an OpenPGP configuration providing
 universal and decentralized civil status to secure your digital life
 (emails, git, ssh, avatar, sso, etc.).
 .
 bl-djibian: System tools for the Debian blend « Djibian ».
 .
 bl-qrkey: Backup or restore OpenPGP ID using printed QR codes and Shamir's secret
 sharing. Configure Yubikeys or Nitrokeys for OpenPGP ID.

Package: bashlibs-dji
Architecture: all
Depends: bashlibs-common, bc, git,
         ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: bash-completion
Description: bash-libs: set of bash executables which may also be sourced as libraries.
 This package contains:
 .
 bl-foopgp: Calculate how many foopgp token (Ɉ) may be created for each cotisations
 to the the foopgp association.
 .
 bl-dji: Manage djis (Ɉ), also known as foopgp tokens.

